-- Heat Defeat Pacers 105-93 to Reach NBA Eastern Conference Finals
-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 2012-05-25T02:43:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-25/heat-defeat-pacers-105-93-to-reach-nba-eastern-conference-finals.html
The Miami Heat beat the Indiana
Pacers 105-93 to reach the National Basketball Association
Eastern Conference finals.  Dwyane Wade  scored 41 points as the Heat won the best-of-
seven playoff series by four games to two. Miami will face the
Boston Celtics or Philadelphia 76ers for a place in the NBA
Finals. Boston hosts Philadelphia May 26 in a decisive seventh
game.  The Heat won their only NBA title in 2006, while the Pacers
havenâ€™t been champion since they claimed a third title in 1973.
Boston won a record 17th championship in 2008, ending a 22-year
gap between titles, while the 76ers secured the last of their
three titles in 1983.  The  San Antonio Spurs  open the Western Conference finals at
home against the Oklahoma City Thunder on May 27.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
